name: Dusk Christmas candle recall
summary: Several popular Christmas candles have been pulled from the shelves at Dusk, Australia's largest homewares retailer, due to safety concerns. The recall was initiated after it was discovered that the candles contained button batteries, posing a significant hazard to children. Button batteries can be easily swallowed and can cause serious internal injuries if ingested. The candles were sold in various scents and sizes and were popular among customers. Consumers are urged to stop using the candles immediately and return them to the store for a full refund.

name: Nissan Honda merger
summary: Automotive giants Honda and Nissan have announced plans to merge, creating an entity that would become the third-largest automaker globally. The move, driven by the demanding and evolving auto market, has raised questions about potential cost reductions for Canadian consumers. Industry experts acknowledge that the merger, prompted by the harsh realities of the auto industry, may not automatically translate into lower prices. Nonetheless, the merger aims to leverage synergies and address challenges in areas such as electric vehicle development and autonomous driving technology. Former Nissan CEO Carlos Ghosn has publicly criticized the merger, labeling it a "desperate move."

name: Cyclone Tracy
summary: 50 years ago, Cyclone Tracy devastated Darwin, marking a turning point in Australia's approach to disaster management. This event prompted the establishment of the Australian Disaster Relief Fund and reforms in building codes and emergency response plans. Survivors recall the eerie aftermath and the lessons learned from this catastrophe, emphasizing the importance of disaster preparedness in the face of cascading disasters. Commemorative media specials, documentaries, and personal accounts are being produced to mark the anniversary, highlighting the enduring impact of Cyclone Tracy and the ongoing need to learn from past tragedies.

name: Liverpool
summary: On December 22, 2024, Liverpool defeated Tottenham Hotspur 6-3 in a thrilling Premier League match. The victory, which was Liverpool's first at Tottenham's new stadium, extended the Reds' lead at the top of the table to four points. Mohamed Salah was the star of the show for Liverpool, scoring two goals and providing two assists. The Egyptian forward became the Premier League's all-time leading scorer with the assist on Liverpool's fourth goal. Tottenham's defeat was their first in the league since August, and it left them in fifth place. The match was also notable for the performance of Liverpool's young attacking duo, Luis Díaz and Salah, who both scored twice. Liverpool's victory was a testament to the strength of their squad, which has been rebuilt in recent seasons under manager Arne Slot. The Reds are now the clear favorites to win the Premier League title, and they will be confident of continuing their good form when they face Southampton in the League Cup on December 23.

name: Eddie Aikau 2024
summary: The 2024 Eddie Aikau Big Wave Invitational, a renowned surfing competition, is set to take place on Sunday at Waimea Bay, Hawaii. Landon McNamara has emerged victorious in the previous competition and will be among the elite surfers competing for the title. Preparations are underway, including parking restrictions along Kamehameha Highway, to accommodate spectators eager to witness the action. Live coverage of the event will be available online and in Ultra HD 4K, offering an immersive experience for surfing enthusiasts.

name: Kevin Andrews
summary: Former Australian Minister Kevin Andrews passed away after a year-long battle with cancer. His funeral was held with the attendance of political figures from both sides of the aisle. Prime Minister and Cabinet organized a state funeral to honor his service. News outlets reported on his passing, highlighting his legacy and the condolences expressed by Tibetan Representative Karma Singey. Articles from news.com.au, ABC News, and Mirage News covered the funeral, focusing on the respect paid to Andrews' unwavering convictions. However, not all articles were solely commemorative, as some commented on the controversial aspects of his political career, questioning the extent of freedom espoused by those who honored him.

name: Christmas Eve
summary: Christmas Eve 2024 will bring varying weather conditions across Canada. Toronto residents can expect a messy weather with snow, while the Maritimes may experience snowy and challenging travel conditions. Several establishments in Toronto will operate on modified hours on Christmas Eve and Christmas Day. Essential services such as hospitals and some public transit will remain open, while most businesses and government offices will be closed. The stock market will also be closed on Christmas Eve. For families celebrating Christmas Eve, there are numerous ways to make the experience special for children, including reading stories, baking cookies, and visiting Santa's workshop.

name: John Pesutto
summary: The Victorian Liberal Party is facing internal turmoil, with multiple MPs seeking a special meeting to vote on leader John Pesutto's future. The division stems from Pesutto's initial decision to readmit MP Moira Deeming to the party, which was met with resistance from some members. Despite subsequent apologies and a new vote, Deeming's bid to return has been blocked. The ongoing conflict has raised questions about Pesutto's leadership, with some members openly expressing their anger. Despite positive polling results, the party's internal divisions continue to threaten Pesutto's position, potentially leading to a leadership spill.
